Diagnosis. Females of the species can be recognised by the narrow copulatory ducts directed at 45 ° towards ST II from the copulatory openings, with the ST II strongly expanded posterolaterally and nearly touching the copulatory ducts (
Fig. 57
). Males can be distinguished by the narrow base of the embolus and the distal section that is approximately three times longer than the basal section (
Fig. 46
).

Distribution. Known only from the Ivory Coast (
Fig. 68
).
